<br>
I break the 4 spawns down into two groups.  Group one is the two wizzies in back and group 2 is the guard and necro.  First thing I do is run to the back and find where lisvan is currently at.  If he's close to the house I go back to the bridge (but do not cross) and make my pet.  If He's close to the bridge  then I run close to the house area finding a secluded spot to make the pet.  If (for example) I have time to sit and med after making the pet before I fight lisvan it only takes a bubble of mana at most to kill him (making sure I ks the pet).  At 54 I can either use 2 char or 3 scars (depending on line of sight) and use up about the same mana.  So for two wizzies I'm usually left with 60% mana left.  Maybe 65%.<br>
<br>
This would be ok if all four were casters.  With their weak hp and making sure I nuke to ks the pet I don't feel I would have any problem at all doing all four before having to med.  The problem is the guard.  Their are three types and they have alot more hp to deal with.  The sk seems the less mr to me as I haven't had to many problems with spells hitting for max damage.  The hardest I think is the warrior that duel weilds.  He has resisted more spells then the other two types (the third type is just a normal warrior).  Doing the guard seems to take up alot of mana, making it difficult to solo all 4 straight out with out medding inbetween.<br>
<br>
This is what I do in order to take out all four with as little down time as possible.  I med after I take out the two wizzies to full then go and take out the guard and necro.  After the necro I don't have to med to full to kill the wizzies, but I med as long as it takes to get the pets health to full.  Sounds simple enough.  The trick is where to med.  The bridge between the wizzie house and the main area where the guard roams is my marker.  If you are on the side of the bridge where the wizzies are the guard won't cross the bridge over to attack you.  And if you are on the side where the guard roams Lisvan won't cross to attack you.  With these npc's at 6 min spawn rate you have plenty of time to med and get pet back to full health before crossing over to fight.  And by the time you cross the npc's you are after are usually up.  Make sure that when you cross you are fully on one side or the other.  If you attack the guard or lisvan while on the bridge and either lisvan or the guard (depending on who you are fighting at the moment) is close they will come and join the fight.  I hope this helps.  If there are flaws in this concept feel free to point them out and give some suggestions to possible solutions.  Like I said before I'm not a super mage.  Any good advice is advice I'm more then happy to have <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Niban Maximus<br>
Level 54 Mage<br>
